<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_bæǧæmsar" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bæǧæmsar</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bæǧænsar</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>с непокрытой головой</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>bare-headed</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_bæǧæmsar." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>Axmæt bæǧæmsuræj fæsdwar wyrdyg læwwydī</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Ахмат с непокрытой головой стоял за дверью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Ahmat stood bare-headed behind the door</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>Axmæt bæǧæmsuræj fæsdwar wyrdyg læwwydī</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Ахмат с непокрытой головой стоял за дверью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Ahmat stood bare-headed behind the door</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ibæǧnæ%i-%isur%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*maǧna-sāra-</w></mentioned>. Подъем гласного во второй части сложного слова (%især%i → %isar%i) обычен (композиционное %ivṛddhi%i), ср. raj-ʒast ‘светлый’ [см. <xr><ref target="#entry_rajʒast"/></xr>] (<xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘глаз’), don-ʒaw ‘водонос’ [см. <xr><ref target="#entry_donʒaw"/></xr> ] (<xr><ref target="#entry_cæwyn"/></xr> ‘идти’), ʒiʒi-daj ‘сосун’ [см. <xr><ref target="#entry_ʒiʒidaj"/></xr>] (<xr><ref target="#entry_dæjyn"/></xr> ‘сосать грудь’). — См. <xr><ref target="#entry_bæǧnæg"/></xr> ‘голый’ и <xr><ref target="#entry_sær"/></xr> ‘голова’; ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_bæǧæmvad"/><ref target="#entry_bæǧæmzæng"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %ibæǧnæ%i-%isur%i ← <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*maǧna-sāra-</w></mentioned>. Vowel alternation in the second part of the complex word (%især%i → %isar%i) is regular (compositional %ivṛddhi%i), cf. %iraj-ʒast%i ‘light’ [see <xr><ref target="#entry_rajʒast"/></xr>] (<xr><ref target="#entry_cæst"/></xr> ‘eye’), %idon-ʒaw%i ‘water carrier’ [see <xr><ref target="#entry_donʒaw"/></xr> ] (<xr><ref target="#entry_cæwyn"/></xr> ‘go’), %iʒiʒi-daj%i ‘suckling’ [see <xr><ref target="#entry_ʒiʒidaj"/></xr>] (<xr><ref target="#entry_dæjyn"/></xr> ‘suck the breast'). — See <xr><ref target="#entry_bæǧnæg"/></xr> ‘bare’ and <xr><ref target="#entry_sær"/></xr> ‘head’; cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_bæǧæmvad"/><ref target="#entry_bæǧæmzæng"/></xr>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>